         <description>Jon Christopher Brown was born on December 3, 1949, in Jersey City, N.J.
            He earned a B.S. degree in botany at the University of Massachusetts-Boston, an M.S.
            degree in botany at the University of Massachusetts-Amherst, and a Ph.D. in biology at
            Tulane University, where he wrote his dissertation on plant communities of the Calakmul
            Biosphere Reserve in Campeche, Mexico. A tobacco enthusiast, Brown became interested in
            Louisiana perique tobacco and has helped revive this dying crop through promotion and
            entrepreneurship with perique farmer, Percy Martin.</description>
